  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SCREEN 3,000 CHILDREN FOR BP &amp; OBESITY IN LAGOS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cardiovascular disease, the leading cause of death, begins during childhood and tracks through adolescents with complications such as stroke and kidney failure. Hypertension, a significant cause of CVD is highly underdiagnosed in children and adolescents in developing countries due to poor skills in the measurement of BP in children. The project will screen 3000 schoolchildren, and train primary healthcare providers on BP interpretation in 2 LGAs in Lagos over 12 months.  Project cost is $49100</narrative>
  </description>
